name: Google I/O 17 Extended Baguio City
description:
Google I/O is the annual global developer conference of Google where they release new products and technologies. Google I/O Extended events focus on bringing the local developer community together to experience Google I/O. This year we'll be having Google I/O Extended Baguio in the University of the Cordilleras on July 8, 2017.

For other Google I/O Extended events in the Philippine's you may visit GDG Philippines' I/O Extended Roadshow website at http://ioextended.gdgph.org/

For more information about Google I/O, you could visit: https://events.google.com/io/

name: Polymer 3.0 Meetup
description:
Join us as we learn on the new features on Polymer 3.0, a lightweight library that helps you take full advantage of Web Components.

Web developers, especially frontend developers, are encouraged to join.

Laboratory Room: F111

Registration starts at 8AM.

See you there!

name: GDG DevFest Baguio 2017
description:
The biggest Google tech conference in Baguio City. All about Android, Web and Cloud

Go to https://developers.google.com/events/devfest/ to know more about DevFests!

name: GDG Campus Roadshow - University of Baguio
Mobile Site Study Jams Roadshow - University of the Cordilleras
description:
• What we'll do
Mobile Site Study Jams is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate the understanding of basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development. The Mobile Sites Certification takes around half a day.

During this event, our Facilitators will guide and teach you the concepts. After the lessons, participants will take the FREE CERTIFICATION EXAM from Google. Participants that complete the exam will receive a printable Google certificate to verify status as a certified mobile sites professional.

• Important to know
This event is exclusive to University of the Cordilleras students only.
